The Herald Herald Correspondent
President of the Russian Federation Vladimir Putin chaired the XII BRICS Summit held recently via videoconference. The summit’s theme was “BRICS Partnership for Global Stability, Shared Security and Innovative Growth”. President Jair Bolsonaro of Brazil, Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India, President Xi Jinping of the People’s Republic of China and President Cyril Ramaphosa of South Africa attended the summit. The heads of state and government of the BRICS countries exchanged opinions on the current state of and prospects for their countries’ cooperation and reviewed the outcomes of the Russian BRICS Chairmanship in 2020. The leaders also reviewed topical international issues and shared their views on the eve of the forthcoming G20 Summit scheduled for 21-22 November. At the end of the summit, the leaders adopted the Moscow Declaration that reflected the consolidated approaches of the BRICS nations to the future development of their interstate group, the Strategy for BRICS Economic Partnership through to 2025  and the BRICS Counter-Terrorism Strategy . The documents are published on the website of the Russian BRICS Chairmanship ://brics-russia2020.ru/.